name: ColorOutputModes
shortdesc: Color output mode options for composites.

property.name: COMPOSITE_LEAVE_UNCHANGED
property.shortdesc: Sends a full-color version of the specified pages to the printer, preserving all color values in the original document. Note: Cannot simulate overprint when using this option.

property.name: COMPOSITE_GRAY
property.shortdesc: Sends grayscale versions of the specified pages to the printer.

property.name: COMPOSITE_RGB
property.shortdesc: Sends full-color versions of the specified pages to the printer.

property.name: COMPOSITE_CMYK
property.shortdesc: Sends full-color versions of the specified pages to the printer. Note: Available only for PostScript printers.

property.name: SEPARATIONS
property.shortdesc: Sends PostScript information for each of the required separations to the printer. Note: Available only for PostScript printers.

property.name: INRIP_SEPARATIONS
property.shortdesc: Allows the printer to create color separations. Note: Valid only with a PostScript raster image processing (RIP) device.
